com.ibm.team.process.common.advice
Interface IProcessReport

All Superinterfaces:
org.eclipse.core.runtime.IAdaptable
All Known Subinterfaces:
IAdvisorReport, IOperationReport, IParticipantReport
public interface IProcessReport
extends org.eclipse.core.runtime.IAdaptable

A report for an element of the process runtime, including operations, advisors, and participants.

Clients may not implement this interface.

Since:
0.5

Method Detail

getSeverity

int getSeverity()
Returns the report's severity. The severity values are as follows:
  • OK - no problems
  • WARNING - a problem which is not serious
  • ERROR - a serious problem

The severity of a report may not be manipulated directly by clients. Rather, severity is computed based on the severity of the reports and infos contained within it. This is generally the maximum severity of any of its children.

More details on the meaning of these values for subclasses are provided in the class comment on IOperationReport and IParticipantReport.

Returns:
the report's severity
